Notifications and unfinished tasks related to your organisation's FSC content will automatically appear on the Tasks and notifications pages. The Tasks page lists those services and channels in your organisation that are about to become outdated. If the content has not been updated for 12 months, it will be archived. You will be reminded of the time limit when 6 months, 9 months and 10 months have passed from when you last saved the content. After the first two notifications, you can clear the task list by pressing the Postpone tasks button. When there are only 2 months left before the content becomes outdated, you can no longer postpone the tasks. The Tasks page view is personal. If you postpone tasks and another user in your organisation does not postpone them, your Tasks lists will show a different number of tasks.

The Tasks page also lists the services and channels that do not have any connections at all. Every service should have at least one channel and every channel should be connected to at least one service.

Notifications about matters that the FSC user should be aware of but which do not necessarily cause a need to make any changes to the FSC content will appear on the Notifications page.

Scroll through the content that is to be approved and check that the information is up to date. If the content requires updating, move the content to editing and correct the out of date information and then save. If the content is correct, select Approve for publication at the bottom of the page. The icon become active only after you have scrolled from the top of the page to its end. You can skip the content that is being checked without approving it by clicking on the Next icon. When you have gone through all the content that is to be approved, click on Publish. If you decide to discontinue approval of contents during bulk publishing, you can publish the contents you have already approved with the Publish icon. If you leave bulk publishing using the Interrupt icon, you will lose all your data.
